      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 170, Number 18 (Wednesday, January 31, 2024)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. McGOVERN:H.R. 7175.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Clause 18 of Section 8 of Article I of the Constitution.The single subject of this legislation is:To protect individuals who face reprisals for defendinghuman rights and democracy by enhancing the capacity of theUnited States Government to prevent, mitigate, and respond insuch cases, and for other purposes.[Page H365]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
